  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering involves several key components:\n\n1. International Regulations\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National Legislation\n- Bank Secrecy Act (USA)\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Suspicious Activity Report (SAR) requirements\n\n3. Key Legal Elements\n- Criminalizing money laundering activities\n- Requiring financial institutions to report suspicious transactions\n- Establishing due diligence procedures\n- Implementing asset seizure and forfeiture mechanisms\n\n4. Compliance Requirements\n- Customer identification procedures\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Risk assessment protocols\n- Regular reporting to financial regulators\n\n5. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Criminal prosecutions\n- Civil penalties\n- Financial institution sanctions\n- International cooperation in investigations\n\n6. Technological Considerations\n- Digital transaction tracking\n- Cryptocurrency regulation\n- Advanced monitoring technologies\n\n7. Penalties\n- Significant financial fines\n- Potential imprisonment\n- Professional licensing restrictions\n\nThe framework aims to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes while maintaining economic integrity.",
